More Minority Writers at Fox: An aggressive search for minority writers for Fox 
television programming has begun, Fox Inc. said Friday. Fox Chairman Barry 
Diller said the goal will be to increase the number of minority writers, and he 
pledged that at least one minority writer trainee will be assigned to each 
series produced by 20th Century Fox Television and for those series aired by 
Fox Broadcasting Co. Like the recent minority writers hiring program announced 
by the Walt Disney Studios, Fox is working with the Writers Guild of America 
