<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New Ojai Fest Head: Englishman Christopher Hunt, who directed the $4.2-million 
Pepisco SummerFare outside New York City, has been named consulting director of 
the three-day, late-spring music festival in Ventura County. Hunt, 43, says his 
goals are to "perpetuate a wonderful tradition" and eliminate an estimated 
$90,000 deficit -- the largest in the festival's history. The red ink came from 
last June's event, which generated less-than-expected ticket revenue, followed 
by a fund-raising shortfall. BETH KLEID 
