<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today is California Admission Day. A small number of businesses and offices 
will be closed in observance of the holidays, including: 
</P>
<P>
* All county offices. 
</P>
<P>
* City offices in Costa Mesa, Laguna Niguel and San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
Other government offices: State and federal offices and county, state and 
federal courts will be open today. Offices in all cities except those listed 
above will be open, also. 
</P>
<P>
Schools: All public schools will be in session today, with the exception of the 
Tustin Unified School District, which begins the new school year on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Banks: All banks and savings and loan institutions will be open on the holiday. 
</P>
<P>
Mail: All post offices will be open, and mail deposited in mail boxes will be 
picked up according to the posted regular schedule. 
</P>
<P>
Trash: There will be regular trash pickup by city and county refuse workers 
today. 
</P>
<P>
Buses: Orange County Transit District buses will run on regular schedule. There 
will be dial-a-ride and car-pool services available on the holiday. 
</P>
<P>
Parks: All city- and county-run parks and recreation facilities will be open 
during regular hours today. 
</P>
