<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
DRIVER HOSPITALIZED AFTER CAR OVERTURNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 25-year-old Oxnard man lost control of his car on Gonzales Road and was 
ejected as it flipped several times before landing in a sod field, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Rubin J. Tamayo, who was driving alone, was in serious condition Sunday in the 
intensive care unit at St. John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard. Tamayo 
suffered broken ribs, a broken collarbone and internal bleeding in the 11:35 
p.m. Saturday crash, a California Highway Patrol spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Tamayo was driving east about 55 m.p.h. when his car left the roadway near 
Victoria Avenue and flipped three times, the CHP said. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
