<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: CAMARILLO; 
</P>
<P>
MOTORCYCLIST SUFFERS SEVERE HEAD INJURIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 23-year-old Port Hueneme man received severe head injuries after his 
motorcycle collided with a car south of the Camarillo Airport, authorities said 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Christopher W. Peacock, 23, was in a coma when he was admitted to Ventura 
County Medical Center after the accident Friday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
A hospital spokeswoman would not say whether Peacock regained consciousness, 
but she said that his condition has improved from critical to serious, and that 
he was in the intensive care unit. 
</P>
<P>
Peacock was driving east on Pleasant Valley Road about 5 p.m. when a car 
turning off Wood Road pulled into his path, a California Highway Patrol 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The impact sent Peacock flying off his motorcycle and onto the pavement. The 
driver of the car, Polonio S. Romero, 31, of Oxnard, escaped injury. 
</P>
<P>
No charges have been filed pending completion of an investigation. 
</P>
<P>
Peacock suffered a broken leg, collarbone and wrist in addition to the head 
injuries, the CHP spokeswoman said. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
