<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: STAB VICTIM REACHES FIREMEN BEFORE DYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A young Glendale man, fatally stabbed during a fight at a Glassell Park 
birthday party, managed to drive himself to a nearby fire station for help late 
Saturday before dying at Glendale Memorial Hospital, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Miguel Noriega, 21, Detective Joe Friend of the 
Los Angeles Police Department said. Friend said it was not clear when the 
stabbing occurred. Reports indicate police were summoned to the hospital about 
12:40 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Friend said reports showed Noriega had attended a birthday party on Verdugo 
Road when he became involved in the fatal fight. 
</P>
