<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASINO SENDS CARDS TO TROOPS IN SAUDI ARABIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Caesars Palace has donated 14,000 decks of playing cards to the American Red 
Cross for shipment to U.S. troops stationed in Saudi Arabia, a resort spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The Las Vegas resort contributed 100 cases of cards at the request of the Red 
Cross station manager at Nellis Air Force Base, Caesars spokesman Phil Cooper 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"When we were made aware of the opportunity to contribute something positive to 
our people who have been sent halfway across the world, we decided to provide a 
special Caesars Palace diversionary tactic," Cooper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
