</P>
<P>
WOMAN HURT WHEN CAR FLIPS ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 22-year-old woman's car overturned, seriously injuring her left wrist and 
hand, in a two-car crash Sunday on the San Diego Freeway, the California 
Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
The CHP said Rebecca George of Laguna Hills was traveling south about 70 m.p.h. 
just north of Jeffrey Road when her car rear-ended a vehicle that had slowed to 
about 40 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
George's car overturned, the CHP said. She was taken to Irvine Medical Center. 
The driver of the other car was not injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
