<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOILED RAGS CAUSE FIRE IN HOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Firefighters quickly extinguished a small blaze in a laundry room of the 
Anaheim Hilton and Towers hotel about 3 a.m. Sunday after some guests were 
evacuated. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was snuffed out in 20 minutes and damage was limited to about $1,500, 
firefighters said. The cause of the fire was attributed to "spontaneous 
combustion of soiled, greasy kitchen rags in a laundry room in the lower lobby 
area." 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials said there was a partial evacuation of the hotel at 777 
Convention Way, but they had no estimate of how many guests were involved. No 
one was injured, they said. 
</P>
<P>
Thirty-six firefighters and six engines responded to the blaze, according to 
Fire Department officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
