</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Teams of divers resumed their search this morning for a Bell Gardens man 
presumed drowned in Castaic Lake. 
</P>
<P>
The 37-year-old man, whose name was not released, jumped from a rented rowboat 
into the water about 5 p.m. Sunday, said Fred Elam, senior lake lifeguard at 
Castaic Lake, about 10 miles north of Santa Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
The man apparently had consumed several beers, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's officials said the man had been seen jumping in the water earlier 
Sunday afternoon and was warned of the danger. 
</P>
<P>
Divers from the county-operated lake and from the Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Department discontinued their search at 6:45 p.m. Sunday, Elam said. 
</P>
<P>
The search resumed at 7 a.m. today with a flight over the lake by a Los Angeles 
County Fire Department helicopter, Elam said. Sixteen divers, working in teams 
of two, resumed the underwater search at 9:30 a.m. 
</P>
