<TEXT>
<P>
Jockey Angel Cordero Jr. has been suspended for seven days by Belmont Park 
stewards for careless riding. 
</P>
<P>
The suspension begins Thursday and goes through Sept. 19. 
</P>
<P>
Cordero was suspended for his ride aboard Naberto in Saturday's fifth race at 
Belmont. 
</P>
<P>
One horse impeded by Naberto was Rubigo, with Chris Antley aboard. Antley 
sustained a lacerated right elbow, after Rubigo fell. Antley is expected to be 
sidelined about a week. 
