<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Poll results -- A story in Sunday's Times Orange County Edition incorrectly 
characterized the nine-point Times Orange County Poll lead that Republican 
State Sen. Marian Bergeson holds in the race for lieutenant governor against 
Democrat Leo T. McCarthy. The margin represents less than a 100,000-vote edge, 
according to pollster Mark Baldassare. 
</P>
</TEXT>
